<dl id="s17020ap"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17020ap">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s17all.htm#s17020ap">sector 20(ap)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> conduction</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If one end of a metal bar is heated the other end soon becomes hot; heat travels along the bar. The flow of heat towards the colder parts of a body without sensible motion of the parts themselves is called <mark>conduction</mark>. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#TBOP"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 128</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
